    <h5>The Scope of Our Service</h5>
    Pangisa provides you with rental booking services ("Services") acting as agents for rental providers and individuals ("Providers"). Pangisa represents the Providers as agents only and accordingly accepts no liability of any kind as a result of any act or omission on the part of the Providers to fulfil their obligations. Your hire of any equipment or vehicle is subject to the terms and conditions of equipment hire imposed by the asset hire Provider. We provide our summary of these Provider terms for your convenience; you are required to agree to the Providers terms on pickup of your vehicle.
    <h5>Common Equipment Rental Provider Terms</h5>
        The renter will be required to supply the following on pickup:
        <br>Proper Identification corresponding to the identification on our website/app.
        <br>Local contact details
        <br>A valid driver’s license where applicable.
    <h5>Forms of payment</h5>
        Rentals will be required to make an initial payment of 25% of the rental period via sasula payment platform, Mobile Money, Momo Pay, Visa, MasterCard, American Express or bank deposit forehand to reserve the equipment. The balance shall be paid before the equipment is collected or delivered. No post payments are acceptable.
5. Deposit / Authority taken on Pickup
The equipment rental providers take a deposit at the start of the rental period to cover preparation of the equipment.


    <h5>Driver Age</h5>
        The minimum age for drives is 20 depending on supplier. There is no maximum age.
    <h5>Additional Drivers</h5>
        Additional drivers may be authorised to drive the vehicle. There is usually a charge per additional driver. Additional drivers must be pre-approved and added on or before pickup.
    <h5>Use of Vehicle/Equipment</h5>
The vehicle may only be driven by the renter or authorized additional driver. The equipment/vehicle may not be driven by the renter:
<br>To transport passengers and/or goods for reward
<br>To propel or tow another vehicle (including caravans and trailers), unless authorized
<br>In motor sport or similar high risk activity

    <h5>Cancellation, Amendment and No Show Fee</h5>
        There is no amendment fee
There is a cancellation fee as per the cancellation policy
10. Extension of Rental / Early Return
Extension of rentals beyond the original date must be authorized by the car hire company. If an extension is required, please contact Pangisa during office hours (weekdays) through our website or the app. If the extension is made directly with the car hire company, then the higher extension rates of the relevant car hire company will be charged. Unfortunately Pangisa are unable to make refunds for vehicles returned early.
    <h5>Insurance Cover</h5>
    Standard insurance cover is compulsory for every vehicle or equipment rented. Insurance cover limits the renter's liability in the event of collision or theft of the vehicle. Additional insurance cover may be purchased which further limits the renter's liability. Personal Belongings are not covered by the insurance provided.
Irrespective of cover purchased the renter will be liable for the full value of the damage and/or loss where such damage or loss is sustained in circumstances including but not limited to the following:
    <br>As a result of driver negligence, malicious or criminal actions of renter or passengers
    <br>Where the vehicle is driven by an unauthorized driver i.e. a driver not specified as a driver or additional driver on the Rental Agreement
    <br>Driving under the influence of alcohol or illegal substances
    <br>Failure to obtain authorization to extend the pre-booked rental
    <br>Where a vehicle is driven on a road or surface not suitable for the vehicle type rented
    <br>Collisions where no other vehicle, person, animal or object is involved
    <br>Where there has been a material breach of the Terms and Conditions of the Rental Agreement
    <h5>Procedures in the event of accident</h5>
<br>If the vehicle is involved an incident, is damaged, stolen or lost, the renter must take every reasonable precaution to safeguard the interests of Pangisa’s supplier, including but not limited to:
<br>Notifying the hire company within 3 hours of becoming aware of the occurrence, and completing the relevant supplier's form within 24 hours
<br>Obtaining the names and addresses of everyone involved and possible witnesses
<br>Not admitting responsibility or liability, not releasing other parties from liability, and not settling or claiming
<br>Reporting all incidents, regardless of value, to the police within 24 hours and supply the car hire company with an accident case number
<br>Making proper provision for the safety and security of the equipment or vehicle
<br>Co-operating with hire company and its insurers in any investigation
    <h5>Additional charges</h5>
<br>Rental companies may offer additional services or charge additional fees for:
<br>Additional equipment: child seat, sixth spare wheel, petrol can or GPS
<br>Delivery & Collection - A delivery and/or collection fee may be levied
<br>Over Border Rentals - Written permission from the hire company is required before taking a vehicle beyond the borders of Uganda. An "over border" fee will be charged by the car company for excursions one of the allowed neighbouring countries. A drop-off charge is levied for rentals terminating outside Uganda
<br>One Way Rentals - a one-way fee may be levied for rentals terminating at a location that is a distance of 150kms or more away from the original renting branch
<br>Fuel - Each hire company or individual shall discuss with the client separately the parameters around the fueling of the vehicle or generator or equipment.
<br>Valet charge may be levied on dirty vehicles
<br>Claim administration fee for traffic fine or insurance claims
<br>Lost Keys - will result in an applicable charge being levied

